explanation: Split the array into k independent subsequences (indices congruent mod k). For each subsequence compute the minimal changes needed to make it non-decreasing by finding the length of the longest non-decreasing subsequence (LIS) and subtracting from the subsequence length. The LIS is found with a greedy algorithm using binary search, giving optimal performance.

